#coordinates
  %h1 Coordinates within 2D Context

  .official.row.py-3
    .col-xs-6
      %h2 The Coordinate System
      %p.pt-2
        The 2D context provided by the canvas has a coordinate system consisting of X and Y values.
      %p
        Starting at the top, left of the canvas is the point (0, 0).
      %p
        As you move down the canvas Y gets larger.
      %p
        As you move right on the canvas X gets larger.
      %p
        So the point (100, 50) means you move right 100 and down 50.


    .col-xs-6
      = image_tag('lessons/coordinates/visual1.png', class: '')


  .simple.row.py-3
    .col-xs-12
      .row
        .col-xs-12
          %h2
            Explore The Coordinate System.
          %p.pt-2
            Mouse over the grey area to the right to see where your mouse is in
            the coordinate system.

        .col-xs-12
          .interactive.row.py-1
            .code-editor.col-xs-6
              %h5
                Editor
                %small (write code below)
              #coordinates_interactive1_editor.editor<
                :preserve
                  var canvas = document.getElementById('coordinates_interactive1');
                  var context = canvas.getContext("2d");

                  context.font= '30px Arial';
                  canvas.addEventListener('mousemove', function(e) {
                    context.clearRect(0, 0, 600, 360);
                    text = 'Your mouse is at (' + e.layerX + ', ' + e.layerY + ')'
                    context.fillText(text, 50, 100);
                  });


              .buttons.py-1
                .run.btn.btn-success
                  Run
                .reset.btn.btn-danger.float-xs-right
                  Reset

            .visual.col-xs-6
              %h5
                Canvas
                %small (your drawing will display here)
              .canvas
                %canvas#coordinates_interactive1



